                        About
                    </button>
                    <div class="modal fade" id="aboutModal" tabindex="-1">
                        <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg modal-dialog-centered">
                            <div class="modal-content">

                                {{!-- Header --}}
                                <div class="modal-header">
                                    <h5 class="modal-title">About First Pick Phonics</h5>
                                    <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal"></button>
                                </div>

                                {{!-- Body --}}
                                <div class="modal-body">

                                    <h6 class="fw-bold mt-2">Phonics</h6>
                                    <p>
                                        Phonics is a method for teaching reading and writing to beginners. Phonics
                                        teaches the
                                        relationship between the sounds of the spoken language and the letters (or
                                        groups of
                                        letters) of the written language.
                                    </p>

                                    <h6 class="fw-bold mt-3">Phonics Rules</h6>
                                    <p>
                                        According to understood.org, about 84% of English words follow the language's
                                        sound-
                                        spelling rules, which are also known as phonics rules. About 50% of words can be
                                        spelled
                                        accurately using sound-symbol correspondence patterns alone, and another 36% can
                                        be
                                        spelled accurately except for one speech sound. The remaining 4% of words are
                                        considered
                                        irregular. These rules can be a helpful tool for beginning readers, struggling
                                        readers, and English Language Learners.
                                    </p>
                                    <h6 class="fw-bold mt-3">The FiRST PiCk Phonics Program</h6>
                                    <p>
                                        This program is specifically designed for students in rural India between the
                                        ages of 8-12
                                        years, although younger children can also benefit from it. It teaches reading
                                        skills by
                                        introducing phonics rules sequentially to beginning readers, using words and
                                        sentences
                                        they are either familiar with or likely to be encountered frequently. All
                                        sentences are
                                        grounded in the rural Indian context. <br>
                                        Reading and comprehension need to go hand in hand. The FiRST PiCk Phonics
                                        Program
                                        integrates phonics instruction with vocabulary instruction using activities,
                                        such as
                                        vocabulary cards, songs, poems, stories, dialogs and plays.
                                    </p>

                                    <h6 class="fw-bold mt-3">Program Designer</h6>
                                    <p>
                                        A learning designer by profession, Puja created online learning programs for
                                        large
                                        organizations for over 20 years before moving back to India and settling down in
                                        Dharamshala. She has been teaching English speaking and reading in the
                                        government
                                        Primary Schools in and around Dharamshala since 2014. A design assignment in
                                        2015 for
                                        an American Teacher Training company got her excited about teaching reading
                                        using
                                        Phonics. The FiRST PiCk Phonics program is her brainchild, which draws from her
                                        extensive
                                        knowledge about learning theories and design principles, and last but not the
                                        least, her
                                        deep love for the children of Rakkar
                                    </p>

                                </div>

